behavior of how Hibernate handles data types like boolean and tinyint can vary
depending on the Hibernate version and the database dialect being used.

IN THIS PROJECT IS USED THE FOLLOWING DEPENDENCIES FOR VALIDATION:
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>
        </dependency>

        INSTEAD OF: Hibernate Validator

        2. STEP
        WHEN YAML FILE USES BOOLEAN IT IS NECESSARY TO USE THE FOLLOWING SYNTAX:
        INSTEAD OF boolean to use BIT


